      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): stage remote media before plugin dispatch",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Stage remote inbound media during dispatch before plugin hook and plugin-bound inbound-claim metadata is built.\n- Mark successfully staged remote media as already staged so the later agent reply path does not restage the same attachment.\n- Add regressions for SCP remote-cache rewriting, plugin-bound Codex claim metadata, and Codex `localImage` turn input.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #91744.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: remote iMessage attachments that start as raw macOS Messages paths are staged before plugin-bound Codex inbound claims are constructed, so the Codex-visible media metadata uses the local remote-cache path instead of `/Users/.../Library/Messages/Attachments/...`.\n- Real environment tested: fresh OpenClaw worktree `/Users/andy/openclaw-91744-imessage-codex-staged-path` based on live `upstream/main` `9a1f2022b127f27312eeb7f57e42d477bddf2c19`, using the actual dispatch source, message hook mapper, and Codex turn-input module from this patch.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node --import tsx --input-type=module` in the worktree to verify the dispatch ordering in source, build the plugin inbound claim event through the real hook mapper, and convert that event through the real Codex turn-input builder.\n- Evidence after fix: terminal output from the runtime command:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"dispatchOrder\": \"stage_remote_media_for_dispatch before deriveInboundMessageHookContext\",\n  \"claimMediaPath\": \"/tmp/openclaw-proof/.openclaw/media/remote-cache/agent-main-imessage/photo.jpg\",\n  \"claimMediaPaths\": [\n    \"/tmp/openclaw-proof/.openclaw/media/remote-cache/agent-main-imessage/photo.jpg\"\n  ],\n  \"codexInput\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"text\",\n      \"text\": \"what is this?\",\n      \"text_elements\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"localImage\",\n      \"path\": \"/tmp/openclaw-proof/.openclaw/media/remote-cache/agent-main-imessage/photo.jpg\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"localImage\",\n      \"path\": \"/tmp/openclaw-proof/.openclaw/media/remote-cache/agent-main-imessage/photo.jpg\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"rawMessagesPathVisible\": false,\n  \"localImagePath\": \"/tmp/openclaw-proof/.openclaw/media/remote-cache/agent-main-imessage/photo.jpg\"\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: the dispatch source now stages remote media before `deriveInboundMessageHookContext()`, the plugin inbound claim metadata carries the staged remote-cache path, and the final Codex turn input contains `localImage` entries for that staged path while `rawMessagesPathVisible` is `false`.\n- What was not tested: a live remote Mac/iMessage conversation, because this environment does not have live remote Mac/iMessage credentials.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nCommands run:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.message-hooks.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.media-policy.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/channel-inbound-roots.contract.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n\nRegression coverage added:\n\n- SCP remote staging success rewrites raw remote iMessage paths to the local remote-cache path.\n- Dispatch stages remote iMessage media before plugin-bound Codex inbound claim metadata is built.\n- Codex turn input uses the staged remote-cache path as `localImage`.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- Did user-visible behavior change? `Yes`\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? `No`\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? `Yes`\n- Highest-risk area: remote media staging now runs earlier in dispatch for remote inbound media, before plugin hooks and plugin-bound claims.\n- Mitigation: the new dispatch staging is gated on `MediaRemoteHost`, a session key, inbound media, and `!MediaStaged`; successful staging marks `MediaStaged` to preserve the single-stage contract for later agent processing. Existing path policy and size checks remain in `stageSandboxMedia()`.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Next action: CI and ClawSweeper review.\n- Waiting on: normal PR checks and durable ClawSweeper verdict.\n- Bot/reviewer comments addressed: implements the issue review direction to stage before plugin-bound Codex claim metadata is derived.\n\nAI-assisted: yes.\n",
